# GoReleaser build output (issue #30).
/dist/

# govulncheck SARIF report (issue #143). Defense in depth, not the actual
# fix: the real fix is running govulncheck in its own job/checkout so it can
# never land in the workspace `goreleaser release --clean` treats as the
# source of truth (see release.yml's header comment, "Round-4 fix") — an
# untracked SARIF there fails GoReleaser's git-dirty check regardless of
# whether it's gitignored (GoReleaser's `CheckDirty` runs `git status
# --porcelain`, which lists untracked files with or without this entry).
# This just keeps it out of `git status`/`git add -A` noise in local dev.
govuln.sarif

# ADR-0011 layer-3 video capture harness (issue #120): captured video/JPEG
# frames/pose-analysis output, and the runtime-only node_modules symlink
# run.sh (and the `test` task's permanent pure-math Vitest suite) creates
# onto web/node_modules (these scripts have no dependencies of their own —
# see test/e2e/capture/run.sh and Taskfile.yml).
/test/e2e/capture/out/
/test/e2e/capture/node_modules

# Claude Code: commit shared subagent definitions (.claude/agents/), but not
